From e282db101b188a8c83e3697109b522a773704936 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Z User <z@container>
Date: Tue, 23 Jun 2026 19:32:03 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: touch injection, canvas stability, save button, resize
 controls
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

4 critical bug fixes:

BUG 1 (CRITICAL): Touch injection not working in games (eFootball)
Root cause: TouchDaemonService defaulted to SOURCE_MOUSE (8194) for
input source. Games like eFootball expect SOURCE_TOUCHSCREEN for touch
input — MOUSE events are ignored or cause unexpected behavior.
Fix: Changed default inputSource to SOURCE_TOUCHSCREEN. Games that
need MOUSE can still select it via profile config.

BUG 2 (HIGH): Canvas mapping mebar/mengecil and changes position
Root cause: Canvas container div lacked overflow-hidden, causing
content to spill out and resize unpredictably on mobile.
Fix: Added overflow-hidden to canvas-container div. Also added
touch-none to resize control buttons for better mobile UX.

BUG 3 (HIGH): Save button no reaction
Root cause: ProfileToolbar Save button called onUpdateProfile which
triggers state update, but no visual feedback was shown to user.
Also, handleUpdateProfile in App.tsx saves to Preferences (async)
but user doesn't see confirmation.
Fix: Added saved state with green checkmark + 'Saved!' text for 2
seconds. Added log message 'Profile saved successfully to storage.'

BUG 4 (MEDIUM): Resize controls hard to reach and disappear
Root cause: Resize controls (↑↓←→ +/−) were positioned at
absolute top-full without centering and had small 24x24px buttons.
On mobile, these were hard to tap and disappeared when clicking away.
Fix: Centered controls with left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2, increased
button size to 28x28px, added backdrop blur + border for visibility,
added touch-none for better mobile touch handling.
